## Design Tokens (Warm A Palette)
 
All new frontend code should use these token classes, not hardcoded colors:
 
- **Backgrounds**: `bg-bg-base` (#1a1918), `bg-bg-surface` (#242220), `bg-bg-elevated` (#2e2b28)
- **Text**: `text-text-primary` (#e8e4df), `text-text-secondary` (#9a958e), `text-text-muted` (#6e6962)
- **Actions**: `bg-action-primary` (#5e8a8a), `bg-action-danger` (#c0564e)
- **Touch targets**: 44px minimum
- **Transitions**: `transition-all duration-200 ease-out`
 
Use `<Button>`, `<Modal>`, `<FormField>`, `<Badge>` from `components/ui/` â€” don't create inline versions.
 
## Naming Conventions
 
- Never use "FINAL" in filenames â€” this project evolves continuously
- Use descriptive names: `fix-cover-text-shadow` not `update-v2`
- Database table is `titles`, not `books`
- API router is `titles.py`, endpoints use `/api/books/` (backward compat)
- UI copy: use "reads," "works," or "titles" â€” not "books" (many items were never physical books)
- Status labels: Unread, In Progress, Finished, DNF (not "Abandoned")
 
## When Making Changes
 
### Before coding:
- Confirm which specific file(s) and function(s) to modify
- Check if the area touches any protected systems
 
### While coding:
- Make the minimum change necessary
- Preserve all existing imports and functions
- Add new code rather than replacing when possible
- Use design system components from `components/ui/` â€” don't create bespoke buttons/modals/forms
 
### After coding:
- List what changed
- Confirm what stayed the same
- Note any side effects or areas to test
- Provide CHANGELOG.md entry text (append at top, never create separate file)
- Provide ROADMAP.md updates if tasks were completed (edit in place, never create patch file)
